HEADWORD: Glooming
<hw>Gloom"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Gloaming</er>.]</ety>
<def>Twilight (of morning or evening); the gloaming.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When the faint <qex>glooming</qex> in the sky⟦br⟧
First lightened into day.</q> <rj><qau>Trench.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The balmy <qex>glooming</qex>, crescent-lit.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gloomth</ent>⟦br⟧
